1
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,936
DOCTOR SHIN

2
00:00:38,939 --> 00:00:39,973
THIS IS A FICTIONAL PRODUCTION

3
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,041
ALL NAMES, LOCATIONS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND CASES ARE FICTITIOUS

4
00:00:41,108 --> 00:00:41,975
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH PARENTAL PERMISSION

5
00:00:44,578 --> 00:00:45,579
EPISODE 5
Hello.

6
00:00:47,648 --> 00:00:48,649
Do I know you?

7
00:00:49,917 --> 00:00:51,251
You're Ms. Marie Yoon, aren't you?

8
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:56,490
Is it true that you offered Velen Kang
a lobbyist position?

9
00:00:58,258 --> 00:00:59,459
I'm not recording you.

10
00:00:59,826 --> 00:01:01,862
I won't write anything about you
without consent.

11
00:01:01,929 --> 00:01:02,930
How can I trust you?

12
00:01:03,697 --> 00:01:04,898
Which hotel employee tipped you?

13
00:01:04,965 --> 00:01:06,233
Nobody, of course.

14
00:01:09,503 --> 00:01:11,605
Is it true
that Mr. Lee U-seul is your son?

15
00:01:15,509 --> 00:01:16,877
Did you hear about the rumor?

16
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:19,880
Does that sound plausible?

17
00:01:19,947 --> 00:01:21,148
That's completely ridiculous.

18
00:01:21,214 --> 00:01:22,749
That's why I'm asking you.

19
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:25,018
Someone tipped me.

20
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,820
What are you here to confirm?

21
00:01:26,887 --> 00:01:28,322
Are you here to ask
about Velen or Lee U-seul?

22
00:01:28,388 --> 00:01:29,489
Who do you work for?

23
00:01:29,556 --> 00:01:30,657
Sungwoo Daily.

24
00:01:30,891 --> 00:01:32,626
I'm Geum Ba-ra from Culture Desk.

25
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:35,095
I've also interviewed Mr. Lee U-seul.

26
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:38,365
Did you read the article?

27
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:40,400
I don't even live in Korea.

28
00:01:40,901 --> 00:01:43,303
How's General Manager Park doing?

29
00:01:44,504 --> 00:01:46,073
He retired last week

30
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:48,675
due to health reasons.

31
00:01:48,742 --> 00:01:49,676
Health reasons?

32
00:01:59,586 --> 00:02:00,621
Ma'am?

33
00:02:13,667 --> 00:02:14,735
Are you okay?

34
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:17,871
Which outlet are you with again?

35
00:02:18,605 --> 00:02:19,906
I'm Geum Ba-ra from Sungwoo Daily.

36
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:23,310
What were we talking about?

37
00:02:26,179 --> 00:02:27,748
<i>She's too old for the orphanage now,</i>

38
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:31,084
<i>so I checked</i>
<i>the Youth Independence Support facilities</i>

39
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:33,353
<i>and found a match for "Kim Jin-ju."</i>

40
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:34,388
Is it a girl?

41
00:02:34,454 --> 00:02:36,089
<i>Yes, and she's 27 years old.</i>

42
00:02:38,692 --> 00:02:39,693
Thank you.

43
00:02:40,394 --> 00:02:41,428
Great work.

44
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,367
<i>Was I thinking too much about Momo?</i>

45
00:02:48,435 --> 00:02:50,937
<i>But why did Ms. Yoon suddenly...</i>

46
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:53,006
How did you manage to interview Ms. Yoon?

47
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:55,742
I just got lucky.

48
00:03:00,747 --> 00:03:02,182
MANAGER FROM SUPPORT FACILITY

49
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:05,318
Hi, Mr. Kim.

50
00:03:05,385 --> 00:03:06,887
<i>Hey, it's been a minute.</i>

51
00:03:06,953 --> 00:03:07,921
Yes.

52
00:03:07,988 --> 00:03:09,723
<i>Brace yourself for what I'm about to say.</i>

53
00:03:10,657 --> 00:03:13,226
<i>Someone came to the office</i>
<i>and asked for your contact info.</i>

54
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,596
<i>He believes you're his long-lost daughter.</i>

55
00:03:17,130 --> 00:03:18,165
Who?

56
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:20,167
<i>He's been abroad for a long time,</i>

57
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:23,303
<i>but you should hear the details in person.</i>

58
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:26,540
<i>Do you want his number?</i>

59
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:28,608
Yes, please.

60
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:29,743
<i>He seems kind.</i>

61
00:03:30,711 --> 00:03:32,679
<i>I can set up a meeting at the office.</i>

62
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,148
Thank you.

63
00:03:43,824 --> 00:03:45,158
- Hello.
- Hello.

64
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:46,493
Jin-ju!

65
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,029
You know it's against the rules
to wear earrings!

66
00:03:54,334 --> 00:03:55,335
Sir.

67
00:03:58,371 --> 00:04:00,040
Please give me my earring back.

68
00:04:00,874 --> 00:04:03,677
It was tucked in with me

69
00:04:04,211 --> 00:04:06,346
when I was left at the orphanage.

70
00:04:07,681 --> 00:04:09,349
I've been wearing it,

71
00:04:10,484 --> 00:04:13,720
thinking my parents
could recognize me with it.

72
00:04:14,554 --> 00:04:16,656
You're so delusional.

73
00:04:17,324 --> 00:04:19,659
How would it be fair
for the other kids, then?

74
00:04:21,294 --> 00:04:23,296
Don't ever wear them in school again.

75
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:26,733
You think they'd come up to you

76
00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:30,570
and admit they abandoned you,
even if they ran right into you?

77
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:33,473
How can he call himself a teacher?

78
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:36,510
I'm still jealous of you.

79
00:04:36,576 --> 00:04:38,211
I have nothing.

80
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:43,617
I would've felt better
if I had anything special like that.

81
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:47,053
I would've also felt less abandoned.

82
00:04:49,156 --> 00:04:51,725
I wonder if they're even alive.

83
00:04:52,359 --> 00:04:53,894
I'll order everything on the menu...

84
00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:56,596
With extra fries...

85
00:05:06,273 --> 00:05:07,974
<i>Hi, I'm Kim Jin-ju.</i>

86
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,076
<i>Can we talk?</i>

87
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:15,649
Hello?

88
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,318
<i>Are you Ms. Kim Jin-ju?</i>

89
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:19,886
Yes.

90
00:05:19,953 --> 00:05:22,522
<i>Did Mr. Kim at the support facility</i>
<i>tell you about me?</i>

91
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:23,657
He did.

92
00:05:23,723 --> 00:05:25,292
Can we meet today?

93
00:05:26,626 --> 00:05:28,762
I don't get off until late. Is that okay?

94
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:30,864
<i>I'm fine even if it's late at night.</i>

95
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:33,533
Can we meet at 9 p.m., then?

96
00:05:37,404 --> 00:05:39,172
Where should I meet you?

97
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:44,811
Please be quiet!

98
00:05:44,878 --> 00:05:46,012
We'll start rolling!

99
00:05:47,047 --> 00:05:47,981
Ready?

100
00:05:49,883 --> 00:05:50,717
Action!

101
00:05:56,389 --> 00:05:57,390
Cut! Start over!

102
00:05:57,457 --> 00:05:58,458
Starting over!

103
00:06:01,895 --> 00:06:03,163
I need to talk to you.

104
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:08,835
Are you here for an interview?

105
00:06:09,469 --> 00:06:10,337
Yeah.

106
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:12,072
Someone called, saying he's my father.

107
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:13,039
He's looking for me!

108
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:15,909
I'm meeting him
at the Sera Hotel Lounge later.

109
00:06:15,976 --> 00:06:17,978
Could you come with?
I'd rather not go by myself.

110
00:06:19,646 --> 00:06:21,414
I have an interview with Jin I-han after.

111
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:26,820
How did he find you?

112
00:06:29,356 --> 00:06:30,357
I know...

113
00:06:32,025 --> 00:06:34,494
all the kids that Ye-jeong bullied...

114
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:39,532
probably think she got what she deserved.

115
00:06:40,934 --> 00:06:43,470
It's my fault for being a bad parent.

116
00:06:44,271 --> 00:06:47,207
Once I found out
what she was doing at school,

117
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:51,645
I should've apologized to all the victims,
no matter how late it was.

118
00:06:52,646 --> 00:06:56,249
I should have tried
to make amends, but didn't.

119
00:06:57,651 --> 00:06:59,753
I know it's too late to regret it now.

120
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:02,856
I don't know what to say.

121
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:07,027
I feel terrible about this, too.

122
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:10,196
We got what we deserved.

123
00:07:11,498 --> 00:07:13,633
They say you should always be kind.

124
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:17,337
I guess the universe
really is watching us.

125
00:07:18,405 --> 00:07:21,775
And it's true you need to use tough love
if you really care.

126
00:07:23,343 --> 00:07:24,644
I wanted to see you

127
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:27,914
because even my father-in-law told me

128
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:33,320
that we should ask you
to become a part of our family.

129
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:36,189
We would like to
officially register you as family.

130
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:40,427
As ridiculous as it sounds,
we want to adopt you.

131
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:44,564
You left a really strong impression on us

132
00:07:44,898 --> 00:07:47,334
the night you visited our home.

133
00:07:48,501 --> 00:07:51,805
You grew up so well,
even without your parents.

134
00:07:51,871 --> 00:07:53,673
We couldn't stop thinking about you.

135
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:57,978
I wish Ye-jeong were half as great as you.

136
00:07:58,778 --> 00:08:02,215
I know we won't see each other
as family immediately,

137
00:08:02,282 --> 00:08:04,117
but we'll grow attached over time.

138
00:08:05,385 --> 00:08:07,954
We'll be the safety net
you can always rely on.

139
00:08:08,588 --> 00:08:09,589
Please let us.

140
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:14,160
This isn't just
to make ourselves feel better

141
00:08:14,627 --> 00:08:16,496
about what Ye-jeong has done.

142
00:08:17,197 --> 00:08:19,466
We just want to support you, that's all.

143
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,202
I'm not as great as you think I am.

144
00:08:23,203 --> 00:08:24,704
I still have a lot to learn,

145
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,241
and you might get disappointed.

146
00:08:28,308 --> 00:08:31,111
You'll never disappoint us
as much as Ye-jeong did.

147
00:08:33,079 --> 00:08:37,083
I really had no idea
she was hurting people like that.

148
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:41,154
I'm not going to think about her anymore

149
00:08:43,089 --> 00:08:44,824
now that she's left us.

150
00:08:46,826 --> 00:08:49,162
I hope her soul is still repenting.

151
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:55,201
What are you going to do?

152
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:58,138
I guess it's obvious.

153
00:09:01,441 --> 00:09:03,443
This was what we always wanted.

154
00:09:06,146 --> 00:09:07,180
That's great.

155
00:09:08,181 --> 00:09:11,284
You'll have a rich family
and educated parents.

156
00:09:12,452 --> 00:09:13,753
I'll take care of you.

157
00:09:14,954 --> 00:09:15,922
How?

158
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,625
By treating me to a meal
from time to time?

159
00:09:21,661 --> 00:09:25,698
They know about you well,
so they'll also care for you.

160
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,069
They did say hi to me
when they came to volunteer last week.

161
00:09:29,135 --> 00:09:31,404
They said they'd continue volunteering.

162
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:34,140
That won't take away our pain.

163
00:09:34,808 --> 00:09:36,743
They're only doing it to feel at peace.

164
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:39,646
We could still learn from that.

165
00:09:39,712 --> 00:09:42,215
None of this would've happened
if they raised their kid right.

166
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:43,983
Ye-jeong was a living devil.

167
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:48,588
I guess...

168
00:09:50,857 --> 00:09:52,392
this is where it ends for us.

169
00:09:52,459 --> 00:09:53,593
Why would it end?

170
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:54,761
It won't.

171
00:09:54,828 --> 00:09:56,362
We'll just be living in different places.

172
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:58,264
But that difference is...

173
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:02,669
You're about to become
the daughter of a lawyer in Seoul.

174
00:10:02,735 --> 00:10:04,737
You'll get everything Ye-jeong had.

175
00:10:06,506 --> 00:10:08,208
Our lives are heading
in opposite directions.

176
00:10:11,845 --> 00:10:12,846
It's great.

177
00:10:14,414 --> 00:10:15,415
I'm happy for you.

178
00:10:18,651 --> 00:10:19,619
I'm happy for you.

179
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,554
What a big surprise.

180
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:23,923
This feels like a dream.

181
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:25,592
I really hope it's actually him.

182
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:37,370
Are you Mr. Kim Yeong-jun?

183
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:39,439
Yes.

184
00:10:46,045 --> 00:10:47,080
Did you have dinner yet?

185
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,549
There's some food on the menu here.

186
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:51,117
Did you have dinner?

187
00:10:55,955 --> 00:10:57,757
<i>How did you get your name, "Jin-ju"?</i>

188
00:10:58,892 --> 00:11:01,594
That's just the name I've gone by
for as long as I can remember.

189
00:11:02,262 --> 00:11:04,097
Did you have a necklace
with your name on it?

190
00:11:06,933 --> 00:11:10,570
I left one on you
when I gave you to a friend in Japan.

191
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:14,174
I do have one earring with pearls
from childhood.

192
00:11:14,574 --> 00:11:15,775
A pearl earring?

193
00:11:16,109 --> 00:11:17,377
It was wrapped with me.

194
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,417
So, I'm not your daughter?

195
00:11:24,484 --> 00:11:26,019
We don't know yet.

196
00:11:27,253 --> 00:11:31,057
Maybe someone took the necklace
and put the earring in.

197
00:11:31,124 --> 00:11:33,493
It's a 14-karat gold earring with pearls.

198
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,727
But it's not expensive.

199
00:11:34,794 --> 00:11:36,829
Did anyone tell you
that you came from Japan?

200
00:11:38,164 --> 00:11:39,098
Me?

201
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:41,367
No.

202
00:11:42,168 --> 00:11:43,536
Anything you can tell me?

203
00:11:43,603 --> 00:11:44,704
Every little clue would help.

204
00:11:47,941 --> 00:11:51,778
The church was closed
when the pastor passed away,

205
00:11:51,844 --> 00:11:55,715
but I was left at the church affiliated
with Nua Children's Home in Myeonghui.

206
00:11:57,483 --> 00:12:00,486
I was left in the baby box.

207
00:12:04,424 --> 00:12:06,993
Most kids at the orphanage
were left at that church.

208
00:12:07,994 --> 00:12:10,597
They either had parents
who couldn't afford to raise them

209
00:12:11,297 --> 00:12:14,100
or came from abusive homes.

210
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:17,170
Was there a note
or anything left with you?

211
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:19,639
No, it was just the earring.

212
00:12:21,307 --> 00:12:22,242
What's your blood type?

213
00:12:23,309 --> 00:12:24,177
It's A.

214
00:12:24,811 --> 00:12:25,645
So is mine.

215
00:12:28,381 --> 00:12:30,316
If your baby was left in Japan,

216
00:12:31,017 --> 00:12:33,853
maybe she's still somewhere there.

217
00:12:34,721 --> 00:12:37,190
No, she was immediately
brought back to Korea.

218
00:12:37,257 --> 00:12:38,291
I looked into it.

219
00:12:40,026 --> 00:12:42,629
We'd better take a DNA test to be sure.

220
00:12:44,697 --> 00:12:45,531
Okay.

221
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:56,009
Did you not see my text?

222
00:12:59,712 --> 00:13:01,714
There's a leak on the second floor.

223
00:13:01,981 --> 00:13:05,018
I told the management,
but they said the owner was abroad.

224
00:13:06,319 --> 00:13:08,221
I can go to a hotel
if I'm making you uncomfortable.

225
00:13:11,758 --> 00:13:15,561
How did your parents react
when you switched your career to acting?

226
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:18,197
My dad didn't even
speak to me for a month.

227
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:20,533
We'll have to see.

228
00:13:35,581 --> 00:13:37,617
I'm sorry I can't drive you.

229
00:13:38,051 --> 00:13:39,819
I can take the subway.

230
00:13:44,724 --> 00:13:46,693
See you on Monday at ten o'clock.

231
00:13:47,527 --> 00:13:48,461
Okay.

232
00:13:54,634 --> 00:13:55,668
Please drive her safely.

233
00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:56,869
Okay.

234
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:17,123
I'll be busy until next week.

235
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,892
Let's meet two weeks from now.

236
00:14:19,959 --> 00:14:21,527
Let's think about it...

237
00:14:24,997 --> 00:14:26,032
Mind if I join you?

238
00:14:30,837 --> 00:14:31,904
I had a meeting here.

239
00:14:33,272 --> 00:14:34,173
He's gone.

240
00:14:34,941 --> 00:14:36,976
- Were you interviewing Jin I-han?
- Yeah.

241
00:14:37,043 --> 00:14:38,911
It almost seemed like a date.

242
00:14:40,279 --> 00:14:42,482
You didn't even look me in the eyes
for my interview.

243
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:44,684
But your eyes were glued to him this time.

244
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:47,186
How can I look elsewhere
when he's answering me?

245
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:49,522
What's with the attitude again?

246
00:14:49,589 --> 00:14:51,257
Maybe I feel annoyed.

247
00:14:51,758 --> 00:14:53,993
Are you annoyed or embarrassed?

248
00:14:55,695 --> 00:14:56,929
Is it because I read through you?

249
00:14:58,164 --> 00:15:01,401
You're back to your old self,
making all these jokes.

250
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:02,535
I'm not joking.

251
00:15:02,969 --> 00:15:05,071
People would've thought
you were on a date.

252
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,209
Let's drink some more.
Tomorrow's Saturday.

253
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,715
We'll take a bottle of Decalar, 25 years.

254
00:15:15,782 --> 00:15:16,616
Yes, sir.

255
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:18,918
Isn't that really pricey?

256
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:22,588
Isn't this heavy?

257
00:15:22,955 --> 00:15:23,956
Yeah, but it's fine.

258
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:27,994
You have a license, right?

259
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:30,563
I know what to get you.

260
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:31,564
When's your birthday?

261
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,905
You have a day you celebrate, right?

262
00:15:40,006 --> 00:15:42,775
You can't get me a car.
It's not like we're that close.

263
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:44,677
We're not that close?

264
00:15:45,578 --> 00:15:47,213
You're really bumming me out today.

265
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:53,186
Did you pick this place?

266
00:15:54,086 --> 00:15:56,622
- No.
- Then I think he's into you.

267
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:58,524
No way. I'm just a journalist.

268
00:15:58,591 --> 00:16:00,259
But you're also a woman.

269
00:16:01,394 --> 00:16:03,796
You get really cold sometimes.

270
00:16:05,131 --> 00:16:06,899
You're the one to talk.

271
00:16:07,366 --> 00:16:09,068
I'm not saying you're cold now.

272
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:12,138
Remember how you left me here
last time, too?

273
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:14,373
I just had an article to write.

274
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,842
Excuses.

275
00:16:15,908 --> 00:16:17,176
I wasn't born yesterday.

276
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:19,579
To be honest...

277
00:16:22,215 --> 00:16:23,916
Put yourself in my shoes.

278
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:24,884
What if...

279
00:16:28,221 --> 00:16:30,389
BA-RA

280
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,668
<i>The caller is unavailable.</i>

281
00:16:42,735 --> 00:16:45,805
<i>Please record your message after the beep.</i>

282
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:57,884
What if I were
completely in love with Dr. Shin,

283
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:00,152
knowing he has Momo?

284
00:17:00,219 --> 00:17:02,321
Wouldn't you think I was being pathetic?

285
00:17:03,823 --> 00:17:04,824
Pathetic?

286
00:17:06,158 --> 00:17:07,360
I'm sure you get it now.

287
00:17:07,426 --> 00:17:09,595
So you thought I was pathetic.

288
00:17:11,497 --> 00:17:12,498
No, it's not the same.

289
00:17:15,001 --> 00:17:16,135
I'll just drink it straight.

290
00:17:30,016 --> 00:17:31,183
It's definitely different.

291
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:32,785
How much does it take
for you to get drunk?

292
00:17:32,852 --> 00:17:33,920
No idea.

293
00:17:33,986 --> 00:17:36,956
Does that mean you can drink a lot
or that you've never gotten drunk?

294
00:17:37,023 --> 00:17:39,659
I need to relax to get drunk,

295
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,494
but I could never
let my guard down like that.

296
00:17:42,128 --> 00:17:43,996
Sometimes, I just acted drunk.

297
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:46,365
I'm great
at secretly throwing away drinks.

298
00:17:46,432 --> 00:17:47,500
Don't throw any away today.

299
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:49,468
It's too expensive for that.

300
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:52,805
Yong-jung.

301
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:54,240
Yeah?

302
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:56,576
Nothing. Just wanted to call your name.

303
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:05,351
Are you going to be tense around me too?

304
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:10,156
Of course not.

305
00:18:10,222 --> 00:18:11,958
And this isn't a business meeting.

306
00:18:15,394 --> 00:18:18,731
When and what makes you happy?

307
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,003
I'm happy right now.

308
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,805
Not now. When else?

309
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:26,706
What about you?

310
00:18:27,073 --> 00:18:29,675
I'm pretty all right right now.

311
00:18:29,742 --> 00:18:30,943
I'm happy,

312
00:18:31,611 --> 00:18:33,245
but you're just all right?

313
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:36,115
"All right" is as good as it gets for me.

314
00:18:43,389 --> 00:18:44,490
Ju-sin...

315
00:18:45,992 --> 00:18:47,560
I can see why women would like him.

316
00:18:48,694 --> 00:18:49,895
Do you like him too?

317
00:18:51,497 --> 00:18:52,331
Yeah.

318
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:55,401
He's the whole package.

319
00:18:58,738 --> 00:19:02,208
He's the son of our amazing Chairman,
though he's passed away now.

320
00:19:03,342 --> 00:19:04,710
Just as the Chairman's son?

321
00:19:11,584 --> 00:19:12,518
Why don't we...

322
00:19:13,586 --> 00:19:14,920
swap homes?

323
00:19:15,888 --> 00:19:17,189
I felt so cozy and at home

324
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:19,558
when I visited your place.

325
00:19:20,693 --> 00:19:22,094
I feel like I'd sleep well there.

326
00:19:23,262 --> 00:19:26,432
It's technically An-hui's home, not mine.

327
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:28,968
You have trouble sleeping?

328
00:19:29,568 --> 00:19:30,936
Yeah, but it's not serious.

329
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:34,674
You'll feel too crammed there
after living in such a big home.

330
00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:38,811
And it'll be the same wherever you go,
if you're on your own.

331
00:19:49,588 --> 00:19:50,790
Pace yourself.

332
00:19:53,826 --> 00:19:55,494
Are you afraid I'll get drunk
and get annoying?

333
00:19:56,128 --> 00:19:57,263
I don't want you to get tired.

334
00:19:59,732 --> 00:20:02,802
Getting tired from drinking isn't tiring.

335
00:20:04,603 --> 00:20:06,872
Don't worry. I'm a tidy drunk.

336
00:20:06,939 --> 00:20:08,140
I've seen enough bad drunks.

337
00:20:08,374 --> 00:20:11,377
I'm sure you'd be cute,
no matter what kind of drunk you are.

338
00:20:11,444 --> 00:20:12,378
At least in my eyes.

339
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:13,979
- I could curse, you know.
- Do it.

340
00:20:14,980 --> 00:20:16,816
I'll even let you beat me today.

341
00:20:20,286 --> 00:20:21,921
There's nothing I like.

342
00:20:21,987 --> 00:20:24,323
You want me to order you something else?

343
00:20:25,357 --> 00:20:27,993
Remember when we first met
by the corner store?

344
00:20:28,961 --> 00:20:29,829
Yeah.

345
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:33,232
I went to the store to buy a snack

346
00:20:33,299 --> 00:20:35,167
to make myself feel better
after my teacher hurt me.

347
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:37,536
But I couldn't buy anything.

348
00:20:42,374 --> 00:20:44,443
<i>All the other kids were with their moms</i>

349
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:47,446
<i>or with their grandmothers.</i>

350
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:54,153
<i>I felt so worthless</i>
<i>compared to all those happy kids.</i>

351
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,160
Let's go to a convenience store.

352
00:21:02,661 --> 00:21:06,298
You need to get yourself a puppy
or find a wife soon.

353
00:21:06,365 --> 00:21:07,933
I can't force myself to find love.

354
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,169
You'll feel at peace and sleep better.

355
00:21:10,503 --> 00:21:13,372
I can read a book
or play video games if I can't sleep.

356
00:21:13,439 --> 00:21:14,507
I have a lot of options.

357
00:21:14,573 --> 00:21:16,342
I want a puppy.

358
00:21:17,576 --> 00:21:18,677
You're lonely, aren't you?

359
00:21:19,378 --> 00:21:20,579
You want me to get you one?

360
00:21:20,646 --> 00:21:23,015
I can't leave the dog home alone all day.

361
00:21:25,351 --> 00:21:26,719
Do you want to move in with me?

362
00:21:28,354 --> 00:21:30,356
I'm serious. I have extra rooms.

363
00:21:33,592 --> 00:21:34,760
Aren't you going to get married?

364
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:37,363
People will think
we live together as partners.

365
00:21:37,429 --> 00:21:38,631
Yeah, we'll live together.

366
00:21:38,697 --> 00:21:40,166
But like a family.

367
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,334
Move in with me.

368
00:21:45,738 --> 00:21:47,206
Are you scared people might judge?

369
00:21:47,273 --> 00:21:49,408
No, because I'll have to move back out.

370
00:21:50,042 --> 00:21:52,077
What woman would like me at your house?

371
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,746
I'd have to get kicked out then.

372
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:57,149
I don't want to
end things with you like that.

373
00:21:58,050 --> 00:22:01,520
As nice as it'd be
to have a dog to rely on,

374
00:22:03,222 --> 00:22:06,325
I just really want someone
I can say "I love you" to.

375
00:22:08,594 --> 00:22:09,929
I've never said it.

376
00:22:12,398 --> 00:22:13,465
Me neither.

377
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:19,405
Have you never said that
to your parents or your brother?

378
00:22:19,471 --> 00:22:20,906
You don't know men, do you?

379
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:22,808
Why would I say that to my brother?

380
00:22:23,876 --> 00:22:25,611
I don't know much about anything.

381
00:22:25,945 --> 00:22:28,080
When my mom passed away,
the worst part was...

382
00:22:30,683 --> 00:22:32,518
that I couldn't tell her I loved her.

383
00:22:34,086 --> 00:22:35,254
I never told her.

384
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:36,822
I guess I chose not to.

385
00:22:37,389 --> 00:22:39,491
I didn't think she'd leave me so suddenly.

386
00:22:40,726 --> 00:22:43,495
You can start now in your heart.

387
00:22:43,562 --> 00:22:45,831
Like a little prayer
before going to bed every night.

388
00:22:46,332 --> 00:22:49,635
She'll definitely hear
her loving son's prayer.

389
00:22:51,237 --> 00:22:52,271
You think so?

390
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:53,706
Yeah.

391
00:22:54,607 --> 00:22:59,278
If I were her, I'd have left my soul
to guard my son forever.

392
00:23:15,461 --> 00:23:17,863
Let me pour some for you.
You're not just anyone.

393
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:21,500
Say that...

394
00:23:23,335 --> 00:23:24,336
again.

395
00:23:28,908 --> 00:23:30,609
You're not just anyone.

396
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:32,511
We're special, right?

397
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:38,651
Gosh, I'm drinking so much today.

398
00:23:48,627 --> 00:23:51,363
You want a puppy
because you want to say, "I love you"?

399
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:52,498
Yes.

400
00:23:52,564 --> 00:23:54,600
I wish I had someone

401
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:57,469
I could give all my heart and love to.

402
00:23:58,470 --> 00:23:59,738
Wouldn't it be better

403
00:24:00,773 --> 00:24:02,274
to say it to me instead of a dog?

404
00:24:08,647 --> 00:24:09,581
I love you.

405
00:24:14,353 --> 00:24:15,387
I'm just kidding.

406
00:24:18,791 --> 00:24:21,493
Dogs only ever care about their owner.

407
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:22,661
They never leave them.

408
00:24:23,762 --> 00:24:25,631
Dogs deserve to be loved.

409
00:24:28,701 --> 00:24:29,735
What am I to you?

410
00:24:30,769 --> 00:24:33,872
I know what you are to me clearly.

411
00:24:36,075 --> 00:24:37,409
So who am I to you?

412
00:24:39,445 --> 00:24:42,081
Am I a little sister
who's six years younger than you?

413
00:24:42,781 --> 00:24:43,916
Someone who won't change.

414
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:47,286
So you want to be a big brother

415
00:24:47,353 --> 00:24:49,521
instead of daddy-long-legs to me?

416
00:24:52,858 --> 00:24:53,892
You are.

417
00:24:54,994 --> 00:24:58,163
The bond we have won't ever change.

418
00:24:58,230 --> 00:24:59,598
We're like family.

419
00:25:01,734 --> 00:25:03,035
We're not even blood-related.

420
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:13,145
Whenever family members would say
"I love you" to each other on TV,

421
00:25:14,246 --> 00:25:16,248
I always...

422
00:25:18,183 --> 00:25:20,452
wondered what it must feel like.

423
00:25:24,023 --> 00:25:25,024
I love you.

424
00:25:28,727 --> 00:25:31,597
My love for you will never change,
my sweet Ba-ra.

425
00:25:36,168 --> 00:25:37,903
Today's the first day
we confessed our love.

426
00:25:38,837 --> 00:25:39,805
Don't forget.

427
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:46,245
Hello.

428
00:25:47,513 --> 00:25:48,414
Oh, my.

429
00:25:50,182 --> 00:25:51,450
I'm at an interview.

430
00:25:52,317 --> 00:25:53,919
He was in the same club
as I was in college.

431
00:25:54,853 --> 00:25:56,855
May I ask for your name?

432
00:25:56,922 --> 00:25:58,791
- I'm Ha Yong-jung.
- I'm Yoo Seon-o.

433
00:26:00,492 --> 00:26:01,960
We're on our second round of drinks.

434
00:26:03,295 --> 00:26:05,097
Have we met somewhere?

435
00:26:06,598 --> 00:26:08,300
Your friends are waiting for you.

436
00:26:08,367 --> 00:26:09,868
We should keep in touch more often.

437
00:26:09,935 --> 00:26:12,371
How come it's so hard to see you
when we work in the same field?

438
00:26:12,805 --> 00:26:13,639
Okay.

439
00:26:14,206 --> 00:26:15,107
All right, then.

440
00:26:16,875 --> 00:26:18,844
Hold on.

441
00:26:18,911 --> 00:26:21,313
Are you...

442
00:26:21,647 --> 00:26:22,581
World Net?

443
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:24,349
I am.

444
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:25,551
What an honor.

445
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:28,487
TAEWON DAILY

446
00:26:28,821 --> 00:26:30,522
Sorry, I don't have one for you.

447
00:26:30,589 --> 00:26:31,657
How about a photo, then?

448
00:26:31,723 --> 00:26:34,393
Come on, Seon-o.
I'm interviewing him right now.

449
00:26:35,594 --> 00:26:38,097
I play <i>Lost Knights</i> all the time!

450
00:26:38,163 --> 00:26:39,198
You owe me a dinner.

451
00:26:39,731 --> 00:26:41,233
- Sure, when--
- You promised.

452
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:43,168
- Okay.
- You're our witness.

453
00:26:45,504 --> 00:26:46,672
- Bye, then.
- Bye.

454
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:56,815
Let's have a proper drink next time.

455
00:27:01,019 --> 00:27:02,121
Please keep this for next time.

456
00:27:02,187 --> 00:27:03,522
- And the bill, please.
- Yes, sir.

457
00:27:04,223 --> 00:27:05,591
You want to visit Ju-sin?

458
00:27:05,657 --> 00:27:06,492
You can go.

459
00:27:06,558 --> 00:27:07,659
No, together.

460
00:27:07,726 --> 00:27:08,660
Why would I go?

461
00:27:08,727 --> 00:27:11,630
It's about time
I introduce you to him as my family.

462
00:27:12,531 --> 00:27:14,433
He wouldn't like that.

463
00:27:15,167 --> 00:27:16,101
Why wouldn't he?

464
00:27:16,435 --> 00:27:18,403
He said he didn't like anyone
crossing lines.

465
00:27:18,604 --> 00:27:20,672
Ju-sin said that to you?

466
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:23,609
He summoned me once.

467
00:27:27,613 --> 00:27:28,480
Get in.

468
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:31,450
Come on, get in.

469
00:27:34,887 --> 00:27:37,589
Try calling him first.
He might be sleeping.

470
00:27:37,656 --> 00:27:41,693
We welcome each other even more
when we show up out of the blue.

471
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,061
We need to set this right.

472
00:27:43,595 --> 00:27:46,398
Maybe he'll be happy to see you,
but I'm different.

473
00:27:46,465 --> 00:27:47,599
Just trust me.

474
00:27:49,835 --> 00:27:50,969
Text him at least.

475
00:28:25,504 --> 00:28:26,572
Be careful.

476
00:28:26,638 --> 00:28:28,240
It's slippery. You might hurt yourself.

477
00:28:34,846 --> 00:28:37,182
I don't want to go.
You should go in alone.

478
00:29:10,882 --> 00:29:12,017
<i>Dr. Shin,</i>

479
00:29:12,317 --> 00:29:15,487
<i>you'll get more media exposure</i>
<i>with the whole wedding announcement.</i>

480
00:29:15,954 --> 00:29:19,157
<i>So I got a suit for you.</i>

481
00:29:19,891 --> 00:29:22,361
<i>I haven't seen you in a suit many times,</i>

482
00:29:22,894 --> 00:29:24,696
<i>but based on my intuition as a stylist,</i>

483
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:26,498
<i>I thought you could do better.</i>

484
00:29:26,565 --> 00:29:27,799
<i>From Jin-ju.</i>

485
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,335
Hurry. I have a wedding to attend.

486
00:29:30,402 --> 00:29:31,470
<i>Okay, Mr. Ha.</i>

487
00:29:34,706 --> 00:29:36,275
What should I wear?

488
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:38,010
The press will be swarming the place.

489
00:29:39,911 --> 00:29:42,814
Mr. Ha told me to bring this to you.

490
00:29:42,881 --> 00:29:44,716
Give it back to him. I can't take it.

491
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:47,119
He loves giving gifts to people.

492
00:29:47,185 --> 00:29:48,320
No, this is too much.

493
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:52,090
Water which is too pure has no fish.

494
00:29:53,759 --> 00:29:54,793
Are you...

495
00:29:55,827 --> 00:29:57,129
lecturing me right now?

496
00:30:05,570 --> 00:30:08,140
<i>Thanks for the suit.</i>
<i>I'll treat you to dinner sometime.</i>

497
00:30:11,009 --> 00:30:14,246
EVERYTHING'S READY FOR THE SURGERY

498
00:30:19,251 --> 00:30:21,853
Did the interview end late last night?

499
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:24,890
So was he your dad?

500
00:30:25,657 --> 00:30:26,792
I hope he is.

501
00:30:26,992 --> 00:30:28,293
He's so young.

502
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:29,961
He had me when he was 20.

503
00:30:30,329 --> 00:30:32,164
We're getting a DNA test done on Monday.

504
00:30:32,531 --> 00:30:33,665
How did he seem to you?

505
00:30:34,099 --> 00:30:36,034
I bet he was handsome back in the day.

506
00:30:36,802 --> 00:30:37,769
And he's single.

507
00:30:38,036 --> 00:30:40,072
Maybe he's a scammer. These days--

508
00:30:40,138 --> 00:30:43,608
Why would he try to scam me
when I have nothing?

509
00:30:44,543 --> 00:30:46,211
We'll do the DNA test,
and if it's not a match,

510
00:30:46,278 --> 00:30:48,814
we'll just say goodbye there and move on.

511
00:30:49,448 --> 00:30:50,449
But...

512
00:30:50,916 --> 00:30:52,217
I feel...

513
00:30:54,886 --> 00:30:56,988
Oh, my! I'd better head back.

514
00:30:57,055 --> 00:30:58,390
If it's Mr. Ha, take this--

515
00:30:58,457 --> 00:30:59,524
No, it's Ms. Yoon.

516
00:30:59,591 --> 00:31:00,425
She's so impatient.

517
00:31:02,427 --> 00:31:03,462
Bye!

518
00:31:30,055 --> 00:31:32,624
KIM JIN-JU

519
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:41,266
<i>Thanks, I got the suit.</i>

520
00:31:41,933 --> 00:31:43,235
<i>Are you free for dinner tonight?</i>

521
00:31:53,545 --> 00:31:55,013
<i>Thanks, I got the suit.</i>

522
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:56,281
<i>Free for dinner tonight?</i>

523
00:31:58,950 --> 00:32:00,051
<i>Yes, I am.</i>

524
00:32:37,622 --> 00:32:39,157
- Ms. Kim Jin-ju?
- Yes.

525
00:32:53,338 --> 00:32:54,206
Did you have lunch?

526
00:32:55,006 --> 00:32:57,242
I had some snacks at a friend's house.

527
00:32:57,709 --> 00:32:58,643
You must be hungry.

528
00:32:59,044 --> 00:33:00,078
What about you?

529
00:33:00,779 --> 00:33:01,713
A friend?

530
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:04,049
Ba-ra?

531
00:33:05,984 --> 00:33:06,818
Yes.

532
00:33:08,186 --> 00:33:09,821
So neither of you has ever dated anyone?

533
00:33:10,655 --> 00:33:11,490
Ever?

534
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:14,659
No.

535
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:16,895
That must be boring.

536
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:20,131
But work is fun.

537
00:33:26,805 --> 00:33:27,672
Ladies first.

538
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:45,257
They're Baccarat glasses.

539
00:33:46,658 --> 00:33:50,395
I figured you wouldn't have much
since you just moved back from Germany.

540
00:33:51,630 --> 00:33:53,131
These will come in handy.

541
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:57,569
When you have clients,
gallery owners, or journalists over.

542
00:33:58,236 --> 00:34:00,605
They'll come to your studio nonstop now.

543
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:07,112
Have you ever had this?

544
00:34:11,082 --> 00:34:12,050
Mr. Kim,

545
00:34:15,420 --> 00:34:16,621
aren't you lonely?

546
00:34:17,489 --> 00:34:20,325
Isn't everyone lonely?

547
00:34:20,759 --> 00:34:22,160
The Chinese character for "human"...

548
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:25,463
has two strokes

549
00:34:26,498 --> 00:34:27,832
leaning on each other like this.

550
00:34:30,702 --> 00:34:33,838
That's how we're meant to live,
supporting one another.

551
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:36,975
That was what my mother used to tell me.

552
00:34:40,812 --> 00:34:41,746
Thankfully,

553
00:34:42,647 --> 00:34:44,482
I at least have a beautiful daughter.

554
00:34:45,784 --> 00:34:46,785
Will you...

555
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:48,687
be my friend?

556
00:34:52,457 --> 00:34:53,491
Just...

557
00:34:54,292 --> 00:34:55,327
a friend?

558
00:34:57,195 --> 00:34:58,597
Someone I can really open up to.

559
00:35:03,401 --> 00:35:06,037
How do you feel about me?

560
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:10,375
Have you ever had this?

561
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:13,478
This wine is on another level.

562
00:35:13,545 --> 00:35:14,913
It's from my personal collection.

563
00:35:20,285 --> 00:35:21,219
Mr. Kim,

564
00:35:21,987 --> 00:35:23,755
I can tell you have your favorites.

565
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:25,657
With Ms. Joo, you were--

566
00:35:25,724 --> 00:35:26,691
Ran-hee.

567
00:35:29,761 --> 00:35:30,929
What do you think you're doing?

568
00:35:31,696 --> 00:35:33,164
- Sorry?
- I'm...

569
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:34,899
Kim Yeong-jun.

570
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:39,404
Or have you forgotten my name?

571
00:35:40,939 --> 00:35:41,773
Wait...

572
00:35:42,907 --> 00:35:43,808
You mean...

573
00:35:49,648 --> 00:35:51,783
No way. You don't...

574
00:35:51,850 --> 00:35:54,452
I got into a huge car accident in Germany.

575
00:35:58,056 --> 00:35:59,090
You totally forgot about me.

576
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:01,760
So you got surgery?

577
00:36:01,826 --> 00:36:03,061
You could've forgotten about me.

578
00:36:05,130 --> 00:36:06,931
But did you also forget
the child you walked out on?

579
00:36:07,399 --> 00:36:09,401
How could you live on without any guilt?

580
00:36:09,801 --> 00:36:10,902
I didn't abandon her! I--

581
00:36:10,969 --> 00:36:12,370
I don't want to talk to you.

582
00:36:14,739 --> 00:36:16,474
I don't ever want to see you again.

583
00:36:16,541 --> 00:36:17,876
Was it Pyeon Seung-jae?

584
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:20,178
His father was a doctor.

585
00:36:20,245 --> 00:36:22,080
He told me you went to Japan.

586
00:36:28,086 --> 00:36:29,154
What about our child?

587
00:36:32,924 --> 00:36:33,925
Is she in Germany?

588
00:36:34,359 --> 00:36:36,728
The daughter of the housemaid
we had for almost half of our lives

589
00:36:37,796 --> 00:36:40,632
succeeded in Japan
and opened a big restaurant there.

590
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:42,233
She was born in my family's house.

591
00:36:43,134 --> 00:36:44,102
I remember hearing that.

592
00:36:44,169 --> 00:36:46,304
I left our child with her
before going to Germany,

593
00:36:46,371 --> 00:36:49,340
but I got into a big accident,
so it took a long time to recover.

594
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:51,476
Then I had to succeed as an artist,
no matter what.

595
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:54,212
So I finally tried
to get in touch after ten years,

596
00:36:54,279 --> 00:36:55,313
but I couldn't.

597
00:36:56,181 --> 00:36:59,317
As anxious as I was,
I thought she'd raise the kid well.

598
00:36:59,751 --> 00:37:01,886
My family had taken
such good care of her, after all.

599
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:05,390
A few years ago,
I managed to find time to visit her,

600
00:37:05,457 --> 00:37:06,691
but the restaurant was gone.

601
00:37:06,758 --> 00:37:08,593
And when I asked the neighboring shops,

602
00:37:10,028 --> 00:37:12,163
I was told she died
a few days after I left.

603
00:37:12,497 --> 00:37:13,331
What happened?

604
00:37:13,398 --> 00:37:14,599
Her mobster boyfriend killed her.

605
00:37:16,134 --> 00:37:17,902
It must've been
a lover's quarrel gone bad.

606
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:20,972
What about our child?

607
00:37:24,809 --> 00:37:26,144
What happened to her?

608
00:37:26,711 --> 00:37:29,614
I managed to find out
that she made it back to Korea.

609
00:37:29,681 --> 00:37:31,349
When? Who brought her in?

610
00:37:31,416 --> 00:37:34,052
There was a Korean lady at her restaurant,

611
00:37:34,486 --> 00:37:35,920
and she brought her to Korea.

612
00:37:35,987 --> 00:37:37,122
What's the lady's name?

613
00:37:37,622 --> 00:37:38,556
How should I know?

614
00:37:38,957 --> 00:37:40,558
I'd only stayed
at the restaurant for a day.

615
00:37:40,625 --> 00:37:42,861
I just remember her with a round face.

616
00:37:44,295 --> 00:37:45,697
Are there no records of her?

617
00:37:51,402 --> 00:37:52,437
I had no idea...

618
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:56,274
I thought...

619
00:37:57,609 --> 00:37:59,177
she was doing well in Japan.

620
00:38:03,548 --> 00:38:05,283
Do you think the lady is raising her?

621
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:06,851
I went to the police

622
00:38:07,552 --> 00:38:11,623
and even hired a private investigator
out of desperation.

623
00:38:14,926 --> 00:38:16,227
He says he can't guarantee anything.

624
00:38:20,532 --> 00:38:22,801
If she's alive, she should be...

625
00:38:26,204 --> 00:38:27,672
Did you never even register her birth?

626
00:38:29,340 --> 00:38:30,575
Are you putting this all on me?

627
00:38:31,276 --> 00:38:34,679
You left me with the child
when my family fell apart and disappeared!

628
00:38:36,047 --> 00:38:39,484
I trusted the maid's daughter
to raise her well, since she adored me.

629
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,189
And I left a necklace with her name on it.

630
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:48,626
What did you name her?

631
00:38:48,927 --> 00:38:50,161
I named her after my grandmother.

632
00:38:51,029 --> 00:38:53,198
Jin-ju.

633
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:58,536
Kim Jin-ju?

634
00:39:05,610 --> 00:39:08,813
<i>Could it be the Kim Jin-ju I know?</i>

635
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:09,881
Hello?

636
00:39:10,648 --> 00:39:11,616
<i>It can't be.</i>

637
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:13,484
Yes, hello.

638
00:39:14,886 --> 00:39:17,222
Yes, I'll check with the gallery.

639
00:39:20,725 --> 00:39:23,795
I've wrapped a painting
in my office beside my desk.

640
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:24,696
Yes, sir.

641
00:39:28,066 --> 00:39:29,200
She must be new here.

642
00:39:29,834 --> 00:39:31,269
She's been Momo's stylist since last week.

643
00:39:31,636 --> 00:39:33,137
You sure you can trust her?

644
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:34,072
Yes.

645
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,442
You know Momo's new stylist?

646
00:39:37,508 --> 00:39:38,509
<i>You mean Kim Jin-ju?</i>

647
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:40,511
Have you done a background check on her?

648
00:39:40,578 --> 00:39:41,412
<i>I haven't.</i>

649
00:39:41,746 --> 00:39:43,047
Get on it, then.

650
00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:44,749
It's a scary world out there.

651
00:39:44,816 --> 00:39:46,651
She might try to dig up dirt on Momo.

652
00:39:47,819 --> 00:39:48,753
Can we trust her?

653
00:39:48,820 --> 00:39:50,555
<i>She doesn't talk much,</i>
<i>and she's quite reserved.</i>

654
00:39:51,089 --> 00:39:52,991
You know how fake people can be.

655
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:54,559
You can never tell.

656
00:39:55,526 --> 00:39:57,829
You know the sponsored bracelet
that went missing last year?

657
00:39:58,363 --> 00:39:59,964
I swear it was an insider job.

658
00:40:01,532 --> 00:40:02,600
What do her parents do?

659
00:40:03,234 --> 00:40:04,535
<i>I don't know that much.</i>

660
00:40:17,949 --> 00:40:18,850
Is it good?

661
00:40:20,184 --> 00:40:21,052
Yes.

662
00:40:21,819 --> 00:40:23,187
Is James good to you?

663
00:40:23,488 --> 00:40:24,322
He is.

664
00:40:24,389 --> 00:40:26,157
Where did you work before Lim Company?

665
00:40:26,591 --> 00:40:29,227
I worked for Ms. Park Min-ja.

666
00:40:31,663 --> 00:40:34,032
"I worked for Ms. Park Min-ja, ma'am."

667
00:40:34,732 --> 00:40:36,434
Show some respect, will you?

668
00:40:37,835 --> 00:40:38,703
I'm sorry.

669
00:40:39,804 --> 00:40:40,939
Get some soda.

670
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:42,640
Everyone drinks that with pizza, right?

671
00:40:42,707 --> 00:40:44,409
I don't drink much soda.

672
00:40:45,343 --> 00:40:46,177
That's good.

673
00:40:46,244 --> 00:40:48,479
It'll be so hard for Momo
to stay away from it

674
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:50,048
if people around her keep drinking it.

675
00:40:50,548 --> 00:40:54,085
It's hard for her to be on a diet
since she loves eating so much.

676
00:40:56,821 --> 00:40:58,122
What do your parents do?

677
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,428
Are they divorced?

678
00:41:07,065 --> 00:41:10,635
I grew up in an orphanage.

679
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:27,151
<i>Don't worry, Ms. Hyun.</i>

680
00:41:27,218 --> 00:41:28,853
<i>I hired her because she works hard.</i>

681
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,888
<i>And you know I have a good eye for people.</i>

682
00:41:31,522 --> 00:41:33,224
<i>I wouldn't just hire anyone for Momo.</i>

683
00:41:38,363 --> 00:41:39,697
We'll have to wait and see.

684
00:41:39,764 --> 00:41:41,532
The way she's so careful around everyone--

685
00:41:41,599 --> 00:41:43,034
Better than someone clueless.

686
00:41:43,101 --> 00:41:44,936
What if she's just a snake in disguise?

687
00:41:45,770 --> 00:41:47,872
You have a habit of doubting everyone.

688
00:41:56,781 --> 00:41:59,217
<i>Tell Jin-ju to come in before she leaves.</i>

689
00:42:10,628 --> 00:42:12,363
Slow down, you'll get indigestion.

690
00:42:13,064 --> 00:42:14,232
Have some milk too.

691
00:42:17,335 --> 00:42:18,903
Did you just come back too?

692
00:42:19,771 --> 00:42:20,605
No.

693
00:42:21,172 --> 00:42:23,841
Did you make these yourself, then?

694
00:42:25,076 --> 00:42:26,978
They're just sandwiches.

695
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:31,249
Jin-ju, your hair is so shiny and thick.

696
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:33,751
Let me compare our hair.

697
00:42:39,123 --> 00:42:41,959
My hair's getting thinner with age.

698
00:42:45,530 --> 00:42:46,531
Mom!

699
00:42:48,199 --> 00:42:49,434
Look at how thick it is.

700
00:43:02,547 --> 00:43:03,648
Why are you so tense?

701
00:43:04,215 --> 00:43:05,316
You're making me tense too.

702
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:11,722
Nice earring.

703
00:43:12,757 --> 00:43:13,858
Drink some.

704
00:43:13,925 --> 00:43:14,992
No, I'd better slow down.

705
00:43:18,963 --> 00:43:19,831
You can't drink much?

706
00:43:20,531 --> 00:43:21,599
Not really.

707
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:23,768
My driver will drive you home.

708
00:43:26,037 --> 00:43:28,439
I can't possibly get in your car...

709
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:29,974
My place is close.

710
00:43:30,508 --> 00:43:31,776
I'll walk from here to sober up.

711
00:43:34,212 --> 00:43:35,246
Was that a gift?

712
00:43:37,448 --> 00:43:39,650
It was in the wrap with me
when I was a baby.

713
00:43:41,719 --> 00:43:43,187
Do you resent your parents?

714
00:43:44,622 --> 00:43:46,958
I'm sure they had a good reason.

715
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:49,760
That's the wiser way to see it.

716
00:43:51,796 --> 00:43:53,631
Does Momo
ever give you a hard time at work?

717
00:43:54,532 --> 00:43:55,666
Not at all.

718
00:43:55,933 --> 00:43:57,635
<i>Man, she was so picky.</i>

719
00:43:58,469 --> 00:43:59,403
Do you have any savings?

720
00:44:00,838 --> 00:44:01,672
I do.

721
00:44:01,739 --> 00:44:02,607
What are you saving for?

722
00:44:03,441 --> 00:44:04,342
A home?

723
00:44:04,775 --> 00:44:07,578
I want to go on a trip first.

724
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:08,479
Where?

725
00:44:09,447 --> 00:44:10,414
To Japan.

726
00:44:10,481 --> 00:44:11,616
For their food?

727
00:44:11,682 --> 00:44:12,550
Or to shop?

728
00:44:12,617 --> 00:44:13,584
Both.

729
00:44:15,620 --> 00:44:16,888
We have a lot more dishes left.

730
00:44:23,161 --> 00:44:24,762
DNA TEST RESULT

731
00:44:29,534 --> 00:44:31,936
DNA ANALYSIS REPORT

732
00:44:41,712 --> 00:44:42,580
Here.

733
00:44:45,783 --> 00:44:46,984
It's a gift certificate.

734
00:44:47,051 --> 00:44:47,919
No, it's fine.

735
00:44:47,985 --> 00:44:50,254
I just had one at home,
and I have no use for it.

736
00:44:51,923 --> 00:44:53,925
Take it. I got something from you too.

737
00:44:56,460 --> 00:44:58,629
But you bought me
such an expensive dinner.

738
00:45:01,599 --> 00:45:02,833
Thank you.

739
00:45:06,871 --> 00:45:08,039
Do you like your job?

740
00:45:09,006 --> 00:45:09,941
Yes.

741
00:45:10,608 --> 00:45:12,310
DNA ANALYSIS REPORT

742
00:45:18,549 --> 00:45:20,985
KIM YEONG-JUN, KIM JIN-JU

743
00:45:21,419 --> 00:45:26,123
THE TESTED DNA SAMPLES DO NOT MATCH

744
00:45:36,801 --> 00:45:39,003
I have a lot of great artwork.

745
00:45:39,070 --> 00:45:41,405
But this costs way too much.

746
00:45:41,472 --> 00:45:43,908
Just consider it a rental, then.

747
00:45:43,975 --> 00:45:45,209
Keep it for a few years.

748
00:45:45,643 --> 00:45:46,544
Mr. Ha.

749
00:45:46,611 --> 00:45:47,578
Yes?

750
00:45:47,645 --> 00:45:51,082
Will you take it back
and continue seeing Yong-jung and me,

751
00:45:51,249 --> 00:45:54,518
or would you like me to take it
and never speak to you again?

752
00:45:56,020 --> 00:45:57,955
Fine, I'll take it back.

753
00:45:58,589 --> 00:46:00,825
Ms. Yoon, take this back to my office.

754
00:46:02,360 --> 00:46:05,429
Gosh, it's impossible to win against you.

755
00:46:05,963 --> 00:46:08,165
You can let your underlings win sometimes.

756
00:46:08,232 --> 00:46:10,134
You're not an underling.

757
00:46:10,201 --> 00:46:12,036
But that was a pretty smooth rejection.

758
00:46:12,103 --> 00:46:14,272
- Get us something to drink.
- Yes, sir.

759
00:46:14,438 --> 00:46:16,474
Aren't you hungry?
Should we order something?

760
00:46:16,540 --> 00:46:17,608
It's snack time.

761
00:46:17,675 --> 00:46:20,011
It'll be my treat this time.

762
00:46:20,111 --> 00:46:22,913
I have to thank you
for all the side dishes you made me.

763
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:24,248
It was my pleasure.

764
00:46:24,315 --> 00:46:25,149
Me too.

765
00:46:26,384 --> 00:46:27,585
What about some pig's trotters?

766
00:46:28,185 --> 00:46:30,087
No, that doesn't suit you.

767
00:46:30,321 --> 00:46:31,455
I'll try it.

768
00:46:31,822 --> 00:46:33,391
You've never had it?

769
00:46:34,659 --> 00:46:35,626
No.

770
00:46:37,028 --> 00:46:38,829
You know what?
Lamb with hummus would be better.

771
00:46:39,363 --> 00:46:40,865
They don't deliver that, do they?

772
00:46:40,931 --> 00:46:41,932
I'm James.

773
00:46:46,704 --> 00:46:48,839
Is Jin-ju on a set?

774
00:47:04,555 --> 00:47:09,093
<i>I should've told you</i>

775
00:47:11,595 --> 00:47:16,600
<i>I loved you</i>

776
00:47:19,537 --> 00:47:24,141
<i>I should've told you</i>

777
00:47:26,110 --> 00:47:31,349
<i>I couldn't live without you</i>

778
00:47:34,018 --> 00:47:38,856
<i>I should've told you</i>

779
00:47:40,691 --> 00:47:46,697
<i>I loved you</i>

780
00:47:48,599 --> 00:47:54,605
<i>I took too long</i>

781
00:47:55,840 --> 00:48:01,812
<i>And you left me</i>

782
00:48:04,248 --> 00:48:06,584
<i>Give my heart</i>

783
00:48:11,555 --> 00:48:14,125
<i>And my tears</i>

784
00:48:18,662 --> 00:48:21,265
<i>Even my dreams</i>

785
00:48:25,436 --> 00:48:30,708
<i>But you went too far away</i>

786
00:48:31,809 --> 00:48:36,914
<i>You're so far away</i>

787
00:48:45,356 --> 00:48:47,558
<i>Should I go and pray at a temple?</i>

788
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:51,162
I just can't give up on her.

789
00:49:13,451 --> 00:49:14,952
All of you...

790
00:49:21,559 --> 00:49:24,261
All of you...

791
00:49:27,064 --> 00:49:28,332
BA-RA

792
00:49:37,975 --> 00:49:39,243
Hey, Ba-ra.

793
00:49:40,478 --> 00:49:41,579
<i>Are you drunk?</i>

794
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:43,714
Just a bit.

795
00:49:45,683 --> 00:49:48,419
How were the DNA results?

796
00:49:52,323 --> 00:49:53,457
We're not a match.

797
00:49:57,061 --> 00:49:58,496
I was never lucky enough.

798
00:49:59,864 --> 00:50:02,333
<i>I got my hopes up over the weekend.</i>

799
00:50:03,067 --> 00:50:04,568
<i>I was so happy.</i>

800
00:50:05,336 --> 00:50:06,170
Go to bed.

801
00:50:06,237 --> 00:50:08,205
<i>Such a cold bitch.</i>

802
00:50:11,442 --> 00:50:13,711
But it's okay that you're cold.

803
00:50:14,512 --> 00:50:15,980
You know

804
00:50:16,046 --> 00:50:17,982
<i>I'll always be your number one fan!</i>

805
00:50:25,322 --> 00:50:26,790
Sly bitch.

806
00:50:57,955 --> 00:50:59,123
Be careful.

807
00:50:59,189 --> 00:51:01,058
It's slippery. You might hurt yourself.

808
00:51:01,125 --> 00:51:03,894
Did you hurt your spine? Your sacrum?

809
00:51:05,429 --> 00:51:06,397
I don't know.

810
00:51:08,799 --> 00:51:09,967
Ju-sin's home.

811
00:51:18,342 --> 00:51:19,176
Sorry.

812
00:51:31,288 --> 00:51:32,556
Are you shocked?

813
00:51:34,658 --> 00:51:35,726
No, why would I be?

814
00:51:45,336 --> 00:51:46,670
I'll get going.

815
00:52:06,657 --> 00:52:07,558
To Myeonghui-dong, please.

816
00:52:07,625 --> 00:52:10,027
We can go to yours first. It's closer.

817
00:52:10,094 --> 00:52:11,228
No, to Myeonghui-dong.

818
00:52:19,069 --> 00:52:20,704
This is why
you should start listening to me.

819
00:52:30,381 --> 00:52:31,682
Is there a convenience store nearby?

820
00:52:31,749 --> 00:52:32,916
There's one everywhere.

821
00:52:35,019 --> 00:52:35,919
Forget it.

822
00:52:37,021 --> 00:52:39,223
Sir, could you go to Itanic Palace first?

823
00:52:39,289 --> 00:52:40,791
No, to Myeonghui-dong.

824
00:52:50,467 --> 00:52:51,402
Here's good.

825
00:52:56,340 --> 00:52:57,341
What would you like?

826
00:53:15,859 --> 00:53:17,094
I'll gain weight if I eat so much.

827
00:53:17,161 --> 00:53:18,128
You need it.

828
00:53:21,098 --> 00:53:22,399
If they fire you for gaining weight,

829
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:24,101
I'll have your back.

830
00:53:25,069 --> 00:53:26,336
I want ice cream too, then.

831
00:53:31,575 --> 00:53:33,444
It's our first time saying
"I love you" to each other.

832
00:53:33,510 --> 00:53:34,812
We should celebrate more.

833
00:53:35,779 --> 00:53:36,780
This is more than enough.

834
00:53:37,781 --> 00:53:39,116
I'm your number one, right?

835
00:53:41,885 --> 00:53:43,554
Being your number three
is good enough for me.

836
00:53:44,388 --> 00:53:47,057
Mr. Ha, Momo, then me.

837
00:53:48,425 --> 00:53:49,259
We don't know that.

838
00:53:51,161 --> 00:53:52,196
Your cab's here.

839
00:53:55,165 --> 00:53:56,100
You should head in.

840
00:54:29,566 --> 00:54:30,768
Good night, my sweet Ba-ra.

841
00:55:24,221 --> 00:55:27,424
<i>What if that orphan nobody</i>
<i>wins over the prince?</i>

842
00:55:29,626 --> 00:55:31,094
Your bones are fine.

843
00:55:32,095 --> 00:55:33,730
Is it a stressed ligament, then?

844
00:55:34,698 --> 00:55:35,999
Should I get some physical therapy?

845
00:55:36,967 --> 00:55:40,070
We'll need specific numbers
of production costs

846
00:55:40,137 --> 00:55:42,272
and how much actors are paid.

847
00:55:42,339 --> 00:55:43,807
And don't just take comments
from promoters.

848
00:55:43,874 --> 00:55:47,010
Speak to a production company's
CEO or executives.

849
00:55:47,077 --> 00:55:47,978
Yes, sir.

850
00:55:48,378 --> 00:55:49,580
- U-seok!
- Yes?

851
00:55:49,847 --> 00:55:51,114
Are you testing my vision or something?

852
00:55:51,582 --> 00:55:54,017
Your articles are quick,
but there are so many typos.

853
00:55:54,084 --> 00:55:55,085
I'm sorry.

854
00:55:57,855 --> 00:55:59,790
I know Director Park Tae-won from Zooplus.

855
00:55:59,857 --> 00:56:01,091
You want his number?

856
00:56:01,158 --> 00:56:02,526
I'd appreciate it.

857
00:56:03,293 --> 00:56:05,662
Tuesdays are my favorite.

858
00:56:05,729 --> 00:56:06,697
Because of the lunch menu?

859
00:56:06,763 --> 00:56:09,233
The cafeteria <i>jjajangmyeon</i>
is better than most restaurant ones.

860
00:56:09,299 --> 00:56:12,035
I hear Sinpyeong Daily
gets beef soup every Friday.

861
00:56:13,704 --> 00:56:14,605
Hello?

862
00:56:15,639 --> 00:56:18,175
Maybe she has a new boyfriend.

863
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:21,411
It said "Mr. Kim from Support Facility."

864
00:56:23,080 --> 00:56:26,750
<i>He knew the exact date</i>
<i>you were left at Minjin Church.</i>

865
00:56:26,817 --> 00:56:29,786
<i>How old is he, approximately?</i>

866
00:56:30,187 --> 00:56:32,623
<i>He was born in 1968,</i>
<i>and his name is Kim Gwang-cheol.</i>

867
00:56:33,290 --> 00:56:34,758
<i>If he's really your dad,</i>

868
00:56:34,825 --> 00:56:37,828
<i>then you'd be Kim Ba-ra, not Geum Ba-ra.</i>

869
00:56:47,938 --> 00:56:51,041
<i>I heard from Mr. Kim</i>
<i>from the Support facility about you.</i>

870
00:56:51,541 --> 00:56:53,510
<i>My name is Geum Ba-ra.</i>

871
00:56:54,645 --> 00:56:55,812
MR. KIM GWANG-CHEOL

872
00:57:14,431 --> 00:57:15,966
MR. KIM GWANG-CHEOL

873
00:57:26,410 --> 00:57:27,477
Hello?

874
00:57:27,544 --> 00:57:30,147
I JUST GOT YOUR TEXT

875
00:57:31,348 --> 00:57:32,482
Hello.

876
00:57:32,549 --> 00:57:35,252
THE SUPPORT FACILITY TOLD ME

877
00:57:35,319 --> 00:57:37,220
YOU LIVE IN SEOUL

878
00:57:37,287 --> 00:57:38,188
Yes.

879
00:57:38,755 --> 00:57:42,859
WHEN ARE YOU AVAILABLE?
I CAN EVEN MEET YOU RIGHT NOW

880
00:57:42,926 --> 00:57:46,229
TELL ME, AND I'LL GO WHERE YOU ARE

881
00:57:46,930 --> 00:57:49,166
IT'LL TAKE LESS THAN HOUR AT MOST

882
00:57:57,541 --> 00:57:59,643
Do they have orthopedics
in the emergency room?

883
00:59:36,506 --> 00:59:37,974
KIM GWANG-CHEOL

884
00:59:57,561 --> 00:59:58,562
Ms. Geum Ba-ra?

885
01:00:11,241 --> 01:00:14,778
Were you left at Minjin Church

886
01:00:15,145 --> 01:00:16,346
on December 21, 1999?

887
01:00:16,813 --> 01:00:17,714
Yes.

888
01:00:19,549 --> 01:00:20,750
Would you like to order?

889
01:00:21,218 --> 01:00:22,119
Coffee, please.

890
01:00:22,452 --> 01:00:23,620
Do you mean an Americano?

891
01:00:24,020 --> 01:00:25,956
- Yes.
- Hot?

892
01:00:26,022 --> 01:00:27,157
No, iced.

893
01:00:28,258 --> 01:00:29,226
I'll have the same thing.

894
01:00:33,130 --> 01:00:36,166
I heard there were two babies
left at the church that day.

895
01:00:36,933 --> 01:00:37,868
Yes.

896
01:01:23,013 --> 01:01:25,849
DOCTOR SHIN

897
01:01:25,916 --> 01:01:28,451
When are you going to stop
speaking so formally to me?

898
01:01:28,518 --> 01:01:29,786
<i>Don't let it become a habit.</i>

899
01:01:29,853 --> 01:01:32,222
Poor Ms. Geum is going to be so shocked.

900
01:01:32,289 --> 01:01:33,423
What do we do?

901
01:01:33,490 --> 01:01:34,391
Are you sure?

902
01:01:34,457 --> 01:01:36,359
But people change their minds.

903
01:01:36,860 --> 01:01:37,928
And she's changed hers.

904
01:01:37,994 --> 01:01:39,529
I could have all of you fired.

905
01:01:39,596 --> 01:01:41,097
Hey, Lee! Park!

906
01:01:41,164 --> 01:01:42,432
Do you want my honest answer?

907
01:01:42,499 --> 01:01:44,167
<i>Of course.</i>
<i>You can't lie with a good drink.</i>

908
01:01:44,234 --> 01:01:46,002
Don't you know the saying, "Know thyself"?

909
01:01:46,069 --> 01:01:47,938
No, I only know love.

910
01:01:48,004 --> 01:01:49,639
Have you ever said "I love you"?

911
01:01:49,706 --> 01:01:50,607
Of course, I loved her.

912
01:01:50,674 --> 01:01:54,277
Once she adopts you,
she'll stop volunteering here, right?

913
01:01:54,344 --> 01:01:55,378
She said she'd keep coming.

914
01:01:55,445 --> 01:01:56,780
Think carefully

915
01:01:56,846 --> 01:01:58,014
- so you don't regret it later.
- I won't.

916
01:01:58,081 --> 01:02:00,650
I was getting educated.
You know what that means, right?

917
01:02:00,984 --> 01:02:02,319
- Jin-ju.
- Yes?

918
01:02:02,385 --> 01:02:03,753
Would you ever get a surgery?

919
01:02:04,421 --> 01:02:08,358
<i>I don't know who will read this first...</i>

920
01:02:08,725 --> 01:02:09,859
<i>How do you feel about me?</i>

921
01:02:09,926 --> 01:02:13,163
<i>Not as the Chairman of the orphanage</i>
<i>or a doctor, but as a man.</i>

922
01:02:13,230 --> 01:02:15,465
I wouldn't dare...

923
01:02:17,934 --> 01:02:19,936
Subtitle translation by Kim Min-sun
